data.chText: 他是利兹或其附近的人。
data.enText: He comes from Leeds or thereabouts.
used to say that a particular number, quantity, time, etc. is not exact

data.chText: 他们买那房子花了大约10万元。
data.enText: They paid $100 000 or thereabouts for the house.

data.chText: （表示即使不完美也很好）差不多
data.enText: used to say that sth is very good, even if it is not perfect

data.chText: 锦标赛结束时，他不拔头筹也差不到哪里去。
data.enText: At the end of the tournament, he'll be there or thereabouts (=he may not win, but he will be one of the best players) .

data.chText: （表示即使不完美也很好）差不多
data.enText: used to say that sth is very good, even if it is not perfect

data.chText: 锦标赛结束时，他不拔头筹也差不到哪里去。
data.enText: At the end of the tournament, he'll be there or thereabouts (=he may not win, but he will be one of the best players) .

example: he stayed in London or thereabouts for several weeks

value.def: You add or thereabouts after a number or date to indicate that it is approximate.

example.ex: He told us that her age was forty-eight or thereabouts...
example.tran: 他告诉我们她的年龄在48岁上下。

example.ex: By 1997 or thereabouts Athens will have a new airport, plus the best underground railway in Europe.
example.tran: 到 1997 年前后，雅典将有一个新机场，还有欧洲最先进的地铁。
